Greed
\f1\b0  is the disordered desire for 
\f0\b Possessions and Wealth
\f1\b0 . As the chapter, "Greed: The Fear of Scarcity," explains, it's rooted in a desire for security. It's the impulse to hoard things (money, status, items) out of a fear that you won't have enough. Its object is 
\f2\i things
\f1\i0 .\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Lust
\f1\b0  is the disordered desire for 
\f0\b People
\f1\b0 . As "Lust: The Longing for Intimacy" describes, it takes the healthy desire for connection and reduces people to objects for selfish, physical gratification, separated from love and commitment. Its object is 
\f2\i people
\f1\i0 .\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Gluttony
\f1\b0  is the disordered desire for 
\f0\b Consumption
\f1\b0 . "Gluttony: The Hunger for Comfort" frames this as using things (like food and drink) to fill a spiritual or emotional void. It's about finding comfort or numbing pain through excess. Its object is the act of 
\f2\i consuming
\f1\i0 .\
